verbose_text: The disorder analysis also revealed that weight (i.e. 10 genes from 19 genes in this pathway) and body mass index (BMI) (i.e. 10 from 23 genes in this pathway) were considered as the most enriched disease processes, which fits well with the known involvement of these two factors in obesity disease, although it also suggests that the contribution of fat mass increase to hyperinsulinism might be due to the expression of insulin by AT and in particular adipocytes.
